Media notes: Juv Barred Owl begging, but then the adult starts calling and flies in with some food and the begging intensifies (listen!)
Observation Details: Pair of fledged juveniles initially spotted on center line of road (!) and got off the road just in time. Adult eventually began calling and came in with food and begging intensified. Magical experience.

Media notes: This is a 5+ min clip of dueting Barred Owls with 3 sets of caterwauling. (from full one hour recording).
Observation Details: a trio of Barred Owls called for over an hour; this 5 min clip included caterwauling. They changed perches, so the last set of caterwauling is closest/strongest (about 35 ft away). It was raining and 50 degrees F.

Media notes: Two BDOW plus songbird alarm calls. Responded to owl call made by me. 13:45 See also ML70041511
Observation Details: I called like a Barred Owl and woke up the first one, who flew over to the trail and began to hoot. Then  the second Barred Owl joined in about five minutes later. On the path to the Community Center.
